   BFN [Text] Changsha, June 19 ( XINHUA ) - - This capital of central China 's Hunan province has been hit by floods in the wake of a succession of rainstorms on the upper and middle reaches of the Xiangjiang River.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   The flood has caused serious losses to people along both banks of the river, especially in Changsha, according to the sources.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   Most of the 15,000 people affected by the flood there have been evacuated to safer places.
